<p>
Japanese people love golf (when they don't watch <em>sumo</em> or baseball)
and it's a status symbol for <em><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Salaryman">salarymen</a></em>.
I guess that they're fascinated by the countless accessories needed for it: the
right clubs, the right bags, the right clothes.. I've seen seven-story golf stores.
</p>

<p>
Among the students in the campus, popular hobbies include making soap bubbles at lunchtime and 
practicing juggling.
