<p>
Here only about 0.5% of the people consider themselves Christian,
so for Christmas - or should I say, <em>kurisumasu</em> -
they're only in for the light decorations 
(which are so <em>sugooooooiii</em>)
and the general atmosphere
of merriness (which is so <em>kawaaaaaaiii</em>).

When the Japanese imported Christmas, they found
themselves with a lot of lights but without a deity, so 
they changed a bit the focus of the holyday
and now Christmas Eve is just like Valentine day in the western 
world - aren't those lights romantic?
</p>

